"/> Find a friend who will go with you and do it for you. You whisper
instructions in his/her ear and let him/her deal with the salesperson.
Perhaps more valuable: start going to yard sales and practice haggling
on stuff that you don't really want so that if your ridiculously low
offer price is refused you can walk away with your head held high.

When you can do this without excessive discomfort, try haggling for
something that you want A LITTLE and see how it goes. Remember, you can
always walk away and you'll never see these people again in your entire
life.

The secret of negotiating is to be able to walk away. It seems like
this shouldn't be difficult with a car -- it's not like they're
one-of-a-kind items.

